==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bobolink
<hw>Bob"o*link`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An American singing bird (<spn>Dolichonyx oryzivorus</spn>). The
male is black and white; the female is brown; -- called also,
<altname>ricebird</altname>, <altname>reedbird</altname>, and
<altname>Boblincoln</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The happiest bird of our spring is the <qex>bobolink</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>W. Irving.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

